OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFood charity sees donations
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffrom supermarkets drop     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Food waste charity Fareshare has told  
OL,6, the BBC it has seen a drop of around   
OL,7, 200 tonnes in supermarket surplus      
OL,8, donations every month this summer.     
OL,10,FThe charity said the reduction had come
OL,11,Fat the same time as demand on the      
OL,12,Fservices they support surged.          
OL,14,FThe BBC understands Fareshare is       
OL,15,Fwriting to major supermarkets, asking  
OL,16,Ffor an increase in contributions.      
OL,18,FTesco, Sainsbury's, Morrisons, Asda and
OL,19,FWaitrose all told the BBC their        
OL,20,Fdonations were steady.                 
